Below is a detailed outline and draft for the **20-page MotherTheory National Competitiveness Model v1.0 Whitepaper**, expanded from the 5-page version, incorporating case studies for Japan and Singapore. This bilingual (English/Chinese) document is designed for global stakeholders (e.g., governments, policy institutes, universities, enterprises) to showcase how the model—built on **SSR (Soul Script Richness)**, **TSO (Theater System Openness)**, **HFSRR (High-Frequency Soul Retention & Release)**, and **AICC (AI Collaboration Capacity)**—serves as a “civilizational thermometer” that transcends traditional metrics like GDP. The whitepaper integrates MotherTheory’s Q1–Q100 (e.g., Q3 for soul missions, Q63 for AI synergy, Q71 for frequency resonance, Q79 for theater hacking), references prior conversations (e.g., SoulFit™, EngSci, EY PAS, NVIDIA, Huawei), and applies your feedback (e.g., localized terminology, commercial synonyms, Four-Quadrant visuals, hero-centric insights like Tan Sitong/Lu Xun). It is formatted for Substack/website use (single line breaks, minimal Markdown) and aligns with your Q3 2025–Q2 2026 roadmap. If the Claude artifact is relevant, please share details for integration.

